    "Html": "\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div id=\"x_x_x_highlighter_445200\">\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><code>&lt;%@ Import Namespace=&quot;MvcMusicStore&quot;%&gt; </code></div>\r\n<div><code>&nbsp;</code>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><code>&lt;%@ Control Language=&quot;C#&quot; Inherits=&quot;System.Web.Mvc.ViewUserControl&lt;</code><code>MvcMusicStore.Models.Album</code><code>&gt;&quot; %&gt;\r\n</code></div>\r\n<div><code>&nbsp;</code>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><code>&lt;</code><code>script</code> <code>src</code><code>=</code><code>&quot;/Scripts/MicrosoftAjax.js&quot;</code>\r\n<code>type</code><code>=</code><code>&quot;text/javascript&quot;</code><code>&gt;&lt;/</code><code>script</code><code>&gt;\r\n</code></div>\r\n<div><code>&lt;</code><code>script</code> <code>src</code><code>=</code><code>&quot;/Scripts/MicrosoftMvcAjax.js&quot;</code>\r\n<code>type</code><code>=</code><code>&quot;text/javascript&quot;</code><code>&gt;&lt;/</code><code>script</code><code>&gt;\r\n</code></div>\r\n<div><code>&lt;</code><code>script</code> <code>src</code><code>=</code><code>&quot;/Scripts/MicrosoftMvcValidation.js&quot;</code>\r\n<code>type</code><code>=</code><code>&quot;text/javascript&quot;</code><code>&gt;&lt;/</code><code>script</code><code>&gt;\r\n</code></div>\r\n<div><code>&nbsp;</code>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><code>Now we use the Html.EnableClientValidation helper method to &quot;turn on&quot; client-side validation. For the both the Create and Edit view templates, add that call directly above the Html.BeginForm call, like so:\r\n</code></div>\r\n<div><code>&lt;</code><code>h2</code><code>&gt;Create&lt;/</code><code>h2</code><code>&gt;\r\n</code></div>\r\n<div><code>&nbsp;</code>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><code>&lt;% Html.EnableClientValidation(); %&gt; </code></div>\r\n<div><code>&nbsp;</code>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><code>&lt;% using (Html.BeginForm()) {%&gt; </code></div>\r\n<div><code>&nbsp;</code>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><code>&lt;</code><code>fieldset</code><code>&gt; </code></div>\r\n<div><code>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</code><code>&lt;</code><code>legend</code><code>&gt;Create Album&lt;/</code><code>legend</code><code>&gt;\r\n</code></div>\r\n<div><code>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</code><span style=\"color:#ff0000\"><strong><code>&lt;%: Html.EditorFor(model =&gt; model.Album, new { Artists = Model.Artists, Genres = Model.Genres })%&gt;\r\n</code></strong></span></div>\r\n<div><code>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</code><code>&lt;</code><code>p</code><code>&gt;\r\n</code></div>\r\n<div><code>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</code><code>&lt;</code><code>input</code>\r\n<code>type</code><code>=</code><code>&quot;submit&quot;</code> <code>value</code><code>=</code><code>&quot;Save&quot;</code>\r\n<code>/&gt; </code></div>\r\n<div><code>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</code><code>&lt;/</code><code>p</code><code>&gt;\r\n</code></div>\r\n<div><code>&lt;/</code><code>fieldset</code><code>&gt;</code></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>plz check these codes.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>I don't know&nbsp;how it works. the list transfers from the lambda expression as the param in EditFor to the ViewData. However, it works well.</p>\r\n",
